Citation.sTitle: Phase equilibria in aqueous two-phase systems containing [Bmim]BF4 and ammonium sulfate/sodium carbonate at different temperatures: Experimental and correlation
Citation.sAbstract: The phase-forming salts and corresponding phase-forming ability for 1-butyl-3-methylimidazolium-tetrafluoroborate ([Bmim]BF4)-based aqueous two-phase were discussed. Experimental liquid + liquid equilibrium (LLE) measurements and the phase diagram have been determined for aqueous two-phase systems containing [Bmim]BF4 and (NH4)2SO4 at T = (298.15, 308.15, and 318.15) K. The Merchuk equation was used to correlate the binodal curves of these systems. Simultaneously, the effects of temperature on the phase-forming ability in the investigated system have also been studied on the basis of a salting-out coefficient obtained from fitting the tie-line data to a Setschenow-type equation for each temperature. Additionally, the phase-forming ability of (NH4)2SO4 and Na2CO3 for [Bmim]BF4-based aqueous two-phase was compared and discussed.
